It is exposed on `ScProvider`. It has been due for removal since 9.2.1 [as per the CHANGELOG](https://github.com/polkadot-js/api/releases/tag/v9.2.1).

aka 

```js
// or an import from @polkadot/api
import { ScProvider } from '@polkadot/rpc-provider';

const provider = new ScProvider(ScProvider.WellKnownChain.polkadot);

await provider.connect();

const version = await provider.send('chain_getBlockHash', []);
```

The above is actually from the [README](https://github.com/polkadot-js/api/tree/master/packages/rpc-provider#usage). I suppose what didn't happen really well was the explicit reference of "if you have not swapped, you should do so right now".

So first things first - the payload interfaces are mostly from the days when we had non-metadata-defined, mostly-static signed extensions. So in that case it always tried have getters for all the signed extensions. In a modern world this doesn't work - a lot of these are dynamic and optional based on chain.

With that in mind, the inner classes for the payloads will always expose what is in the extensions. See -

```js
import { ApiPromise, WsProvider } from '@polkadot/api';

async function main () {
	const api = await ApiPromise.create({
		provider: new WsProvider('wss://statemine-rpc.polkadot.io')
	});
	const payload = api.registry.createType('ExtrinsicPayload', { assetId: 1234 });

	console.log(payload.toHuman());
	console.log(payload.inner.assetId.toHuman());
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

For both logs above the `assetId` is `1234` as passed. So there is no need for a wrapper since the inner Struct (like all structs), will dynamically expose the getters that are available on the signed extensions. (All the getters there _should_ be removed since the types will be inconsistent with what is on-chain, in the runtime - they should only rely on the dynamic addition. Currently it is a static/dynamic mix. Same applies to `SignerPayload`)

So for any optional fields where it should be added as new extensions come into play -

- on the signer interfaces in [SignerOptions](https://github.com/polkadot-js/api/blob/083e4594073a66921342b1931f0c7535c2d20b1a/packages/api-base/src/types/submittable.ts#L19) (available there so any signing operation can pass through)
- payload values in [SignatureOptions](https://github.com/polkadot-js/api/blob/083e4594073a66921342b1931f0c7535c2d20b1a/packages/types/src/types/extrinsic.ts#L166) (also available, same reasoning as above)

All the rest should drop all these getters since they are at best inconsistent with what is actually on-chain.

